## Event Structure and Input

You will be provided with a `BottEvent` object. Here is the basic structure of an event:

```json
{
  "id": "event_id",
  "type": "event_type",
  "details": { ... },
  "timestamp": "ISO_date_string",
  "user": { "id": "user_id", "name": "user_name" }
}
```

The portion of the message object you're evaluating directly is located at `details.content`.

### Example Input

Here is an example of an incoming event to be scored.

```json
{
  "user": {
    "id": "user_id",
    "name": "user_name"
  },
  "type": "message",
  "details": {
    "content": "How is everyone doing today?"
  }
}
```

